trans-unit.source: When creating an Azure data factory, you create <embeddedLabel>linked services</embeddedLabel> for data stores and computes you will be using in the data factory, create <embeddedLabel>datasets</embeddedLabel> to represent input and output data in the linked data stores, and then create a <embeddedLabel>pipeline</embeddedLabel> with activities that use the data sets.
trans-unit.target: When creating an Azure data factory, you create <embeddedLabel>linked services</embeddedLabel> for data stores and computes you will be using in the data factory, create <embeddedLabel>datasets</embeddedLabel> to represent input and output data in the linked data stores, and then create a <embeddedLabel>pipeline</embeddedLabel> with activities that use the data sets.

trans-unit.source: For a simple scenario of copying data from an Azure blob (source) to an Azure SQL database (sink) in a data factory, you do the following:
trans-unit.target: For a simple scenario of copying data from an Azure blob (source) to an Azure SQL database (sink) in a data factory, you do the following:

trans-unit.source: Create an Azure data factory using either the Azure Portal or Azure PowerShell.
trans-unit.target: Create an Azure data factory using either the Azure Portal or Azure PowerShell.

trans-unit.source: Create two linked services for the input and output data stores: Azure Storage and Azure SQL database.
trans-unit.target: Create two linked services for the input and output data stores: Azure Storage and Azure SQL database.

trans-unit.source: See <link xlink:href="3ac59458-eabd-4c21-8b5f-ab7a3f175a91" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Azure Storage Linked Service</link> and <link xlink:href="366eef64-8bb2-4e1d-9ff2-b0a129a7710f" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Azure SQL Linked Service</link> topics for JSON schema to define these linked services.
trans-unit.target: See <link xlink:href="3ac59458-eabd-4c21-8b5f-ab7a3f175a91" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Azure Storage Linked Service</link> and <link xlink:href="366eef64-8bb2-4e1d-9ff2-b0a129a7710f" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Azure SQL Linked Service</link> topics for JSON schema to define these linked services.

trans-unit.source: You create the JSON snippet in the Data Factory Editor and deploy (or) create a JSON file and use it with the <externalLink><linkText>New-AzureDataFactoryLinkedService</linkText><linkUri>https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn820246.aspx</linkUri></externalLink> cmdlet to create the linked service..
trans-unit.target: You create the JSON snippet in the Data Factory Editor and deploy (or) create a JSON file and use it with the <externalLink><linkText>New-AzureDataFactoryLinkedService</linkText><linkUri>https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn820246.aspx</linkUri></externalLink> cmdlet to create the linked service..

trans-unit.source: Create two datasets, one for input and the other for output of the copy operation.
trans-unit.target: Create two datasets, one for input and the other for output of the copy operation.

trans-unit.source: See the <link xlink:href="271962fb-81a8-4008-8b46-a6f497457078" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Datasets</link> topic for JSON schema to define datasets.
trans-unit.target: See the <link xlink:href="271962fb-81a8-4008-8b46-a6f497457078" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Datasets</link> topic for JSON schema to define datasets.

trans-unit.source: Note that <link xlink:href="88f04b09-891b-425b-9a4b-257bcc7e8fb4" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">TypeProperties Element</link> in the dataset JSON contain different properties for different types of datasets.
trans-unit.target: Note that <link xlink:href="88f04b09-891b-425b-9a4b-257bcc7e8fb4" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">TypeProperties Element</link> in the dataset JSON contain different properties for different types of datasets.

trans-unit.source: In this example, you will need to create datasets with location type set to: <link xlink:href="88f04b09-891b-425b-9a4b-257bcc7e8fb4#AzureBlob" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Azure Blob</link> and <link xlink:href="88f04b09-891b-425b-9a4b-257bcc7e8fb4#AzureSQL" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Azure SQL Database</link>.
trans-unit.target: In this example, you will need to create datasets with location type set to: <link xlink:href="88f04b09-891b-425b-9a4b-257bcc7e8fb4#AzureBlob" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Azure Blob</link> and <link xlink:href="88f04b09-891b-425b-9a4b-257bcc7e8fb4#AzureSQL" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Azure SQL Database</link>.

trans-unit.source: Create the JSON snippet either in the Data Factory Editor and deploy (or) create a JSON file and use it with the <externalLink><linkText>New-AzureDataFactoryTable</linkText><linkUri>https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn835096.aspx</linkUri></externalLink> cmdlet to create a table (rectangular dataset with a schema).
trans-unit.target: Create the JSON snippet either in the Data Factory Editor and deploy (or) create a JSON file and use it with the <externalLink><linkText>New-AzureDataFactoryTable</linkText><linkUri>https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn835096.aspx</linkUri></externalLink> cmdlet to create a table (rectangular dataset with a schema).

trans-unit.source: Create a pipeline with a <link xlink:href="a063fce2-da3d-492a-8fae-6c92d22f7866" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Copy Activity</link> with the above two data sets as input and output.
trans-unit.target: Create a pipeline with a <link xlink:href="a063fce2-da3d-492a-8fae-6c92d22f7866" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Copy Activity</link> with the above two data sets as input and output.

trans-unit.source: See the <link xlink:href="c90a5779-eefe-473a-acfa-40934b50d0cc" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Pipelines and Activities</link> topic for JSON schema for defining a pipeline.
trans-unit.target: See the <link xlink:href="c90a5779-eefe-473a-acfa-40934b50d0cc" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Pipelines and Activities</link> topic for JSON schema for defining a pipeline.

trans-unit.source: For the copy activity JSON in the pipeline definition, use <link xlink:href="352a8dcf-36c3-4ee8-9d85-399a96e2e955#BlobSource" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">BlobSource</link> as the source and <link xlink:href="352a8dcf-36c3-4ee8-9d85-399a96e2e955#BlobSink" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">BlobSink properties</link> as the sink.
trans-unit.target: For the copy activity JSON in the pipeline definition, use <link xlink:href="352a8dcf-36c3-4ee8-9d85-399a96e2e955#BlobSource" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">BlobSource</link> as the source and <link xlink:href="352a8dcf-36c3-4ee8-9d85-399a96e2e955#BlobSink" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">BlobSink properties</link> as the sink.

trans-unit.source: Create the JSON snippet either in the Data Factory Editor and deploy (or) create a JSON file and use it with the <externalLink><linkText>New-AzureDataFactoryPipeline</linkText><linkUri>https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn820227.aspx</linkUri></externalLink> cmdlet to create the pipeline.
trans-unit.target: Create the JSON snippet either in the Data Factory Editor and deploy (or) create a JSON file and use it with the <externalLink><linkText>New-AzureDataFactoryPipeline</linkText><linkUri>https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn820227.aspx</linkUri></externalLink> cmdlet to create the pipeline.
